FBIS4-23993 "drafr119_e_94014" FBIS-AFR-94-119 Daily Report 16 Jun 1994 WEST AFRICA Nigeria Federal Government Declares Airports Safe Federal Government Declares Airports Safe AB1606224494 Lagos Radio Nigeria Network in English 1500 GMT 16 Jun 94 AB1606224494 Lagos Radio Nigeria Network English BFN [Text] The Federal government has reassured the international community of the safety of the Nigerian airports. The minister of transport and aviation, Mr. Ebenezer Babatope, gave the assurance at a seminar. Mr. Babatope said the government had taken necessary precautions to ensure adequate security at the airports, pointing out that security standards outlined by the International Civil Aviation Organization had been complied with. The minister said the arrangement had been finalized for the signing of bilateral air service agreements with Poland, South Africa, and some countries in the former Soviet Union.
